---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import floraWarmBg from '../../assets/images/flora-warm-bg.jpeg';
---

<Layout title="Komyo ReikiDo - Core Self Reiki">
  <main class="bg-[#FAF8F5] min-h-screen">
    <section class="relative w-full h-[10vh] sm:h-[12vh] max-h-[110px] overflow-hidden">
      <img
        src={floraWarmBg.src}
        alt="Core Self Reiki - Warm Floral Background"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover object-center"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-black/10 to-transparent"></div>
    </section>
    {/* Page Quote */}
    <section class="bg-[#F5F1EB] py-10 sm:py-12 border-b border-[#E5E0D8]">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-4xl text-center">
        <blockquote class="font-serif text-xl sm:text-2xl text-[#2C1810] mb-4 text-balance italic">
          Go placidly<br />
          In the midst of praise or blame!
        </blockquote>
        <p class="text-lg text-[#5A5A5A] italic">
          (Komyo ReikiDo motto)
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Content Section */}
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-4xl">
        
        {/* Page Title */}
        <div class="mb-16 text-center">
          <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-[#2C1810] mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight">
            Komyo ReikiDo
          </h1>
          <div class="w-20 h-1 bg-[#dd2728] mx-auto"></div>
        </div>

        {/* Core Text */}
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="font-serif text-[#5A5A5A] leading-relaxed text-justify text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-2xl mb-6 lg:mb-8">
            Buddhist monk Hyakuten Inamoto is the founder of the Kyoto Healing Centre where he holds weekly classes and Reiki shares for both Japanese and foreign students.
          </p>

          <p class="font-serif text-[#5A5A5A] leading-relaxed text-justify text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-2xl mb-6 lg:mb-8">
            Although officially belonging to the Jodo-Shu or Pure Land branch of Japanese Buddhism, Inamoto Sensei is an independent monk who seeks authentic spiritual experiences. When asked about his temple or monastery, Inamoto Sensei answers in his typical wise yet humorous fashion: “I do not live in a temple or monastery. I am the temple. People are the temple. My temple is where I am. It is a mobile temple.”
          </p>

          <p class="font-serif text-[#5A5A5A] leading-relaxed text-justify text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-2xl mb-6 lg:mb-8">
            Komyo ReikiDo, the system Inamoto Sensei has created, emphasizes both the therapeutic aspect and the spiritual aspect of Reiki Ryoho (the healing of the body and the mind, as well as the realization of the state known as Anshin Ritsumei, or enlightenment).
          </p>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#2C1810] mb-4">The Motto and Philosophy</h2>
            <p class="font-serif text-[#5A5A5A] leading-relaxed text-justify text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-2xl mb-6 lg:mb-8">
              The motto of Komyo ReikiDo, “Go placidly in the midst of praise or blame” intends to remind practitioners that through Reiki Ryoho, we are accessing non-dual conscious vibration and that our ability to do so depends on our capacity for inner stillness. Furthermore, although lineage is important, in Komyo ReikiDo, deeds are the criteria of a good Reiki practitioner and teacher. What one does, speaks, and thinks, how one lives one’s life on a day to day basis, is considered to be of primary importance. This understanding is supported by Buddhist philosophy.
            </p>
            <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-[#dd2728] pl-6 my-8 font-serif text-[#5A5A5A] text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-2xl italic">
              According to Dhammapada, Everything whatsoever has the mind as the source. The mind is the master builder and of the mind is everything made. If with an impure mind, one speaks or acts, suffering follows him in the same way as the wheel follows the ox that draws the cart. The mind is the master builder and of the mind is everything made. If with a pure mind, one speaks or acts, happiness follows him like his shadow that never leaves him.
            </blockquote>
          </div>

          <p class="font-serif text-[#5A5A5A] leading-relaxed text-justify text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-2xl mb-6 lg:mb-8">
            Inamoto Sensei learned Reiki from Mrs. Chiyoko Yamaguchi who had trained with Dr. Chujiro Hayashi, one of Usui Sensei’s original students.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-[#F5F1EB] p-8 rounded-lg mt-12 border border-[#E5E0D8]">
            <p class="font-serif text-lg lg:text-xl text-[#5A5A5A] italic mb-0">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Elyssa Matthews received training from Hyakuten Inamoto Sensei for whom she co-ordinates Reiki Master classes in Toronto. She has also studied Gendai Reiki Ho with Hiroshi Doi in Toronto and in Ashiya, Japan. Her first master initiation into Reiki had been facilitated by Martin Stock.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-16 relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-[#E5E0D8] max-w-xl mx-auto">
            <div class="absolute inset-0 z-0">
              <img 
                src={floraWarmBg.src} 
                alt="" 
                class="w-full h-full object-cover object-center opacity-15"
              />
              <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-white/40"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="relative z-10 p-8 sm:p-10 text-center">
              <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-[#5A5A5A] leading-relaxed mb-0">
                To find out more about <a href="/coreselfreiki/lineage/reiki-ryoho" class="text-[#7C3F47] hover:underline font-medium">Reiki Ryoho</a>,<br />
                to book a <a href="/coreselfreiki/services/private-sessions" class="text-[#7C3F47] hover:underline font-medium">Reiki session</a>,<br />
                or to sign up for a <a href="/coreselfreiki/services/group-classes" class="text-[#7C3F47] hover:underline font-medium">course</a>,<br />
                please <a href="/coreselfreiki/contact" class="text-[#7C3F47] hover:underline font-medium">contact</a> Elyssa Matthews.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
